- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper focuses on the hardware architecture of a quantum circuit fabric technology (ion-trap) and proposes an algorithm to optimize the mapping of a quantum algorithm to this architecture.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for scheduling, placement, and routing of a quantum algorithm, which involves data structures and algorithms.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses a software tool that accompanies the proposed algorithm for scheduling, placement, and routing of a quantum algorithm. This tool could potentially involve programming languages.
- cs.OC (Optimization and Control): The paper proposes an algorithm to optimize the mapping of a quantum algorithm to a specific quantum circuit fabric technology (ion-trap), which involves optimization and control.
